  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Toss the porcini mushrooms with olive oil, garlic, rosemary, thyme, salt, and pepper in a large bowl until they're evenly coated.",
    "Transfer the mushroom mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish and top with crumbled goat cheese, shredded mozzarella, and grated Parmesan cheese.",
    "Bake the dish in the preheated oven for 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Remove the dish from the oven and let it cool for 5 minutes before serving."
